      About Us
   NCI-Frederick is located within the Ft. Detrick U.S. Army base in
   Frederick, Maryland, and is the Department of Health and Human
   Service’s only government-owned, contractor-operated facility. More
   than 100 principal investigators located here direct research aimed at
   exploring the causes of cancer, AIDS, and related diseases.

   Whether you are a first-time visitor to our site, or a Federal or
   contractor employee, we want to provide you with helpful information
   related to:



   Visitor Information
   Driving directions (from DC, Baltimore, VA, and PA); local and campus
   maps; security policies and procedures; links for visitors to other
   pages of interest such as the Campus Directory and the NCI
   Bethesda/Frederick shuttle service

   Contact Information
   Contact information for research laboratories, cancer information,
   cancer trials, and the NCI-Frederick webmaster

   Administrative Offices and Services
   NCI management offices and Administrative Resource Centers (ARCs), SAIC
   Frederick Contracts and Administration Office, policies and procedures,
   technology development and commercialization

   Contractors
   Four on-site contractors provide support to investigators in
   scientific, technical, and operations management (SAIC Frederick);
   Scientific Library services (Wilson Information Services Corporation),
   computer and statistical expertise (Data Management Services); and
   animal production  (Charles River Laboratories).

   History
   The origin and development of NCI-Frederick, which began operations
   under the auspices of the NCI in June 1972

